  description:
    en: 'distribution of co-benefits - Cost type: air_pollution - Stakeholder: citizens
      - 2023: 0.4 - Metric: distribution of co-benefits - Majority attributed to healthcare
      given a large amount of the damages caused by air pollution is a cost that the
      healthcare system needs to bear. Some is also attributed to citizens (improved
      well-being, reduced sick days, longer life)<br/>distribution of co-benefits
      - Cost type: air_pollution - Stakeholder: property_owners - 2023: 0.0 - Metric:
      distribution of co-benefits - Do we need to confirm with cities?<br/>distribution
      of co-benefits - Cost type: air_pollution - Stakeholder: cities - 2023: 0.0
      - Metric: distribution of co-benefits - Yes<br/>distribution of co-benefits
      - Cost type: noise - Stakeholder: citizens - 2023: 0.7 - Metric: distribution
      of co-benefits - Majority attributed to citizens given majority of benefits
      include increased psychological well-being. This also results in some cost savings
      for healthcare<br/>distribution of co-benefits - Cost type: noise - Stakeholder:
